    <description>Participants will complete four, one-hour training sessions in which they will perform a single task each session</description>
    <arm_group_label>Pure Task Training</arm_group_label>
  </intervention>
  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  If you have had a Traumatic Brain Injury (TBI)or no history of neurological
             disease/damage.

          -  If you are between the ages of 19 and 65.

        Exclusion Criteria:

        For participants with Traumatic Brain Injury:

          -  If you have a history of prior neurological disorders (e.g., stroke, seizures, or
             brain tumor).

          -  If your Brain injury is less than 6 months ago.

        For healthy participants:

        -If you have a history of prior neurological disorders (e.g., head injury, stroke,
        seizures, or brain tumor).

        For All participants:

          -  If you have significant psychiatric history (such as schizophrenia or bipolar
             disorder.)

          -  If you have a alcohol or drug abuse history.

          -  If you are currently taking certain types of medications, which the study doctor will
             review.

          -  If you do not have a working knowledge of the English Language.
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
